competent individuals to showcase their problem-solving, critical thinking, and domain expertise. Successful performance in this examination is often a determining factor in the initial screening phase, paving the way for further interviews and assessments before candidates can be considered for potential employment roles within the esteemed company.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"infosys-exam-date\">Infosys Exam Date <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Candidates can check the table below to learn more about the Exam details of Infosys 2024. The Application form is open. Therefore, you can start applying for the Infosys Exam.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Infosys Exam 2024<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Details<\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Exam Date <\/td><td>To be Announced<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Application<\/td><td>Open<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-are-the-infosys-exam-eligibility-criteria\">What are the Infosys Exam  Eligibility Criteria?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Infosys Exam is exclusively for the graduates who completed their undergraduate in Btech, M.sc in IT \/Computer Science. Candidates can check out the Infosys Eligibility Criteria table provided below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Infosys Exam Eligibility Criteria <\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Information Details <\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Batch <\/td><td>2024<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Education Qualification<\/td><td>B.E\/B.Tech, M. Tech and M.sc graduates in Computer Science\/Information Technology<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Backlog <\/td><td>No<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Percentage Criteria <\/td><td>65% or 6.5 CGPA or above&nbsp; in Xth, XIIth, and Graduation<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Moreover, only those candidates who meet the eligibility criteria provided here can apply for the Infosys exam. Freshers without work experience can apply for the Infosys exam to get a job there. The Infosys exam is crucial to the company&#8217;s recruitment process, allowing them to identify and hire talented individuals. While the exam assesses candidates&#8217; skills and aptitude, certain eligibility criteria must be met, including an age limit. According to the guidelines set by Infosys, candidates appearing for their employment exam must fall within the age range of 18 to 35 years.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s important to note that the age limit is calculated as of the date specified in the official exam notification released by Infosys. Candidates falling outside the prescribed age range may find their applications ineligible for consideration, even if they possess the required qualifications and skills.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Practice for Infosys Exam with <a href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/infosys-mock-test\/\">Mock test by Skillvertex<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"infosys-exam-pattern-2024\">Infosys Exam Pattern 2024<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p> Graduates\/ Postgraduates of Btech, who completed the MSC in Computer Science can check out the Exam Pattern 2024 provided below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Infosys Syllabus  Section<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>No of Questions <\/strong><\/td><td><strong>Total Time <\/strong><\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Logic<\/td><td>15 Questions<\/td><td>25 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Mathematical Ability<\/td><td>10 Questions<\/td><td>35 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Verbal Ability<\/td><td>20 Questions <\/td><td>20 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Pseudo Solving<\/td><td>4 Questions<\/td><td>10 Mins<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Puzzle Code<\/td><td>5 Questions<\/td><td>10 Mins <\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Total <\/td><td>54 Questions <\/td><td>100 Mins ( 1hr 40 minutes )<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Infosys has updated its exam syllabus for 2024 to hire freshers. Infosys Exam Questions will be difficult this year. So, candidates should prepare and focus more on the Infosys Exam Syllabus, to understand the Exam pattern. The syllabus of the Infosys Exam 2024 includes Mathematical Ability, Logic, Verbal Ability, Pseudo Code, and Puzzle Solving. The total Questions in the Infosys Exam is 54 and the Infosys Exam duration &#8211; 1 hour 40 minutes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"what-is-the-infosys-interview-process\">What is the Infosys Interview Process?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To get a job at Infosys, you need to go through these steps:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Online Test<\/strong>: First, you&#8217;ll have to take an online exam. This test will check your skills &#8211; logical thinking, English, math, and coding (depending on the job role). The questions can be quite difficult.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Technical Interview<\/strong>: If you clear the online test, you&#8217;ll be called for a technical interview. Here, experts from Infosys will assess your technical knowledge and problem-solving abilities related to the job role.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>HR Interview<\/strong>: The final round is an interview with Infosys&#8217;s human resources team. They will evaluate your overall personality, communication skills, and fitment for the company&#8217;s culture.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Performing well in all three rounds is crucial to get hired by Infosys. The online test and interviews are designed &#8211; to assess your skills and potential for the job.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, the Infosys exam is a demanding test that assesses various technical and non-technical skills. Clearing this exam requires extensive preparation, dedication, and a deep understanding of the concepts covered. However, the effort put in is well worth it, as success in this exam can open doors to exciting career opportunities at Infosys, a leading global IT services company. With perseverance and a strategic study approach, aspirants can increase their chances of cracking this challenging exam. Ultima